WEBVTT

00:15.265 --> 00:17.972
No, there's so much blood here.

00:19.937 --> 00:22.599
Damn it. Still not enough light.

00:22.773 --> 00:25.560
Harold: I turned them all up
as high as they'll go.

00:26.610 --> 00:29.647
Never mind.
Frannie, wipe my forehead off.

00:29.821 --> 00:31.812
I'm sweating like a pig.

00:33.158 --> 00:34.944
Fran: You okay?

00:48.090 --> 00:51.503
Wait a minute. Give me the scissors.

00:53.095 --> 00:54.631
Can you see it, east Texas?

00:55.973 --> 00:58.009
Stu:
That's his appendix right there.

00:58.600 --> 01:00.306
Dayna: Stu?

01:01.395 --> 01:03.056
Stu: No, the small one.

01:03.772 --> 01:04.978
Stu?

01:05.774 --> 01:06.774
Stu?

01:06.942 --> 01:08.853
What, dayna, what?

01:10.320 --> 01:11.856
You don't need to.

01:12.030 --> 01:14.271
What do you mean?
We're almost there.

01:15.242 --> 01:16.573
He's dead, St...

01:19.246 --> 01:21.328
Please

01:22.541 --> 01:24.497
cover him up.

01:47.649 --> 01:51.858
I am the resurrection and the light.

01:52.613 --> 01:58.324
Whosoever believeth in me
shall not perish.

02:00.078 --> 02:04.321
There's more, I suppose,
but I don't remember it

02:04.499 --> 02:07.707
it worked for me, judge. Amen.

02:07.836 --> 02:09.372
Amen.

02:21.850 --> 02:23.431
Hey.

02:49.670 --> 02:51.331
Good morning, Mr. lauder.

02:51.963 --> 02:53.373
Where the hell is everybody?

02:53.548 --> 02:56.631
Dayna's still asleep.
I don't know where Fran is.

02:56.760 --> 02:58.751
I think stu went fishing.

02:58.929 --> 03:01.636
Off catching lunch
in the big two-hearted river.

03:01.807 --> 03:03.388
Figures.

03:03.517 --> 03:05.428
I beg pardon?

03:05.852 --> 03:07.217
Oh, nothing.

03:07.354 --> 03:09.595
The judge and I thought
we'd take a little ride into town

03:09.773 --> 03:10.773
and go cb shopping.

03:10.941 --> 03:12.351
Wanna come?

03:12.526 --> 03:14.266
I'll pass.

03:14.444 --> 03:16.184
Just as you like.

03:52.816 --> 03:54.181
Hi

03:54.860 --> 03:56.270
Hi

03:56.486 --> 03:58.226
Still thinking about Mark?

03:59.239 --> 04:01.230
It's not just that.

04:01.950 --> 04:04.987
I had a dream
with the scary one last night.

04:05.120 --> 04:07.486
It was by far the worst one yet.

04:07.664 --> 04:10.952
There were all these crosses
on highway 15.

04:11.126 --> 04:14.789
Oh, yeah. Made out of barn beams
and telephone poles, right?

04:14.921 --> 04:16.832
With people hanging off of them.

04:17.007 --> 04:18.042
You too?

04:18.258 --> 04:19.258
Yeah

04:19.426 --> 04:24.420
and dayna and Glen, judge farris.

04:24.806 --> 04:25.966
Okay if I sit down?

04:26.183 --> 04:29.425
Yeah of course.

04:33.440 --> 04:35.726
I dreamed about him
the night Mark died.

04:36.318 --> 04:38.354
Last night, I drew the old lady.

04:38.570 --> 04:40.811
Oh, that one's much better.

04:41.031 --> 04:42.362
Yeah, a whole lot better.

04:42.532 --> 04:46.571
She was on a porch,
but it's not the same one as before.

04:46.703 --> 04:49.866
I think she and the first bunch
have finally made it to Boulder.

04:50.040 --> 04:51.905
Oh, I know they have.

04:53.627 --> 04:55.333
She said:

04:55.837 --> 04:58.499
"You got to move them along
faster still, Stuart.

04:58.673 --> 05:00.709
One day off's all you get.

05:00.884 --> 05:03.296
Mind you, keep picking up strays
along the way."

05:05.222 --> 05:07.213
It's so weird.

05:07.390 --> 05:10.507
How can we all be having
the same dream like this?

05:13.438 --> 05:15.224
I don't know.

05:24.825 --> 05:28.659
Uh, you know,
Glen's got some sleeping pills

05:28.829 --> 05:30.990
in his little traveling pharmacy.

05:31.122 --> 05:32.658
You want me to ask him
to give you one?

05:33.792 --> 05:34.998
Thank you, but no.

05:35.168 --> 05:39.332
You sure? You'll get a good night's rest
before we have to hit the road again.

05:39.756 --> 05:41.417
I can't.

05:42.259 --> 05:43.795
Why not?

05:46.388 --> 05:48.128
I'm afraid it'll hurt the baby.

06:21.965 --> 06:23.956
Have you told Harold?

06:29.848 --> 06:31.634
When are you due?

06:32.058 --> 06:33.798
January.

08:46.401 --> 08:47.857
Harold?

08:50.113 --> 08:52.695
We have something to tell you. Um...

08:55.410 --> 08:57.526
I don't know really how to say it.

08:57.746 --> 09:00.078
I think I have a pretty good idea.

09:00.707 --> 09:03.039
Congratulations.

09:05.295 --> 09:07.160
Fran thought you might be a little...

09:07.338 --> 09:10.171
Harold: Jealous? Angry?

09:10.967 --> 09:13.128
Something like that, yeah.

09:13.553 --> 09:15.509
Harold: Well, jealous, yeah.

09:15.680 --> 09:17.261
Angry...

09:17.682 --> 09:19.422
That's life.

09:26.816 --> 09:29.023
I've got something to tell you.

09:31.613 --> 09:34.650
Couldn't say it up until now.

09:37.952 --> 09:39.442
I love you, frannie.

09:43.458 --> 09:45.289
Thank you, Harold.

09:46.252 --> 09:47.992
And I believe I owe you an apology.

09:48.129 --> 09:50.791
Hey, that's all right.

09:52.425 --> 09:53.631
Still friends, right, guys?

09:53.843 --> 09:55.754
Of course. Stu: Yeah

09:55.929 --> 09:57.669
(00d deal.

10:02.227 --> 10:03.763
You need any help with that?

10:03.978 --> 10:05.593
No, everything's under control.

10:05.772 --> 10:07.478
You sure, now?

10:23.164 --> 10:25.280
Perfectly under control.

11:10.003 --> 11:12.164
My life for you!

11:33.484 --> 11:36.567
Cibola.

11:39.032 --> 11:41.318
Seven-in-one.

11:41.534 --> 11:44.241
My life for you.

11:50.877 --> 11:52.208
How are you feeling, man?

11:53.504 --> 11:55.586
I'm okay.

11:56.758 --> 11:57.758
Who are you?

11:57.926 --> 11:59.882
This here is Lloyd henreid.

12:00.011 --> 12:02.377
He ain't bad
for a slice of wonder bread.

12:02.555 --> 12:03.761
I'm the rat-man.

12:03.932 --> 12:05.968
Bold, black, beautiful.

12:06.142 --> 12:09.509
Pleased to meet you, trash.

12:09.687 --> 12:12.019
How'd you know people back home
used to call me that?

12:12.190 --> 12:15.899
Gotta do something about
that talking-in-your-sleep thing.

12:17.403 --> 12:18.813
Listen.

12:19.822 --> 12:23.781
I didn't know your exact sizes,
but these ought to be okay.

12:23.993 --> 12:25.824
Am I going somewhere?

12:26.037 --> 12:27.322
Yeah. Flagg wants to see you.

12:29.249 --> 12:32.741
My life for him. Yes.

12:32.919 --> 12:34.284
My life for him.

12:35.546 --> 12:38.128
Dude's crazy.

12:39.509 --> 12:41.249
I ike we're not?

12:42.929 --> 12:44.135
Get dressed.

13:13.001 --> 13:14.866
Flagg: The trashcan man.

13:15.920 --> 13:17.956
How good it is to see you.

13:18.631 --> 13:23.921
My life for you.

13:24.095 --> 13:26.131
I don't think it'll come to that.

14:14.270 --> 14:17.262
There's work for you in the desert,
trash.

14:18.399 --> 14:19.730
Great work if you want it.

14:19.859 --> 14:22.771
Anything. Anything.

14:24.364 --> 14:26.730
My life for you.

14:38.211 --> 14:39.326
I love you.

14:40.088 --> 14:43.580
I know. I know you do.

14:46.427 --> 14:49.885
And I'm gonna
fulfill all your dreams, trash.

14:51.349 --> 14:52.759
Come.

14:54.435 --> 14:56.596
Let's talk about your future.

15:19.127 --> 15:21.083
Fran: Mother abagail.

15:21.254 --> 15:23.336
I dreamed about you.

15:24.215 --> 15:27.002
I know you did.

15:29.387 --> 15:31.469
Come on up here.

15:32.849 --> 15:36.467
Just you and your man to start with.

15:37.103 --> 15:38.593
Come on.

15:39.480 --> 15:41.971
You're with child, little girl.

15:42.150 --> 15:43.606
How did you know that?

15:45.987 --> 15:47.773
How do, Stuart?

15:47.989 --> 15:48.989
Welcome to Boulder.

15:49.157 --> 15:50.363
Fran: Nice to meet you, Ralph.

15:50.491 --> 15:53.324
Ralph: Nice to meet you.
That there's Susan stern.

15:53.453 --> 15:55.614
Fran: Good to meet you, Susan.
Susan: Hi

15:55.788 --> 15:57.244
how'd you know my name?

15:59.750 --> 16:02.537
You're all welcome here.

16:02.753 --> 16:07.122
Come on in. Let's us visit a spell.

16:07.300 --> 16:11.418
Seems there were more here before.

16:14.056 --> 16:15.762
Harold's gone.

16:18.227 --> 16:21.560
Well, come on in, now.
I made some lemonade.

16:21.731 --> 16:23.722
Farris: Very pleased to see you.

16:26.152 --> 16:28.143
I'm here.

16:28.321 --> 16:30.562
I came to you.

16:32.325 --> 16:34.486
Flagg:
The bride cometh to the bridegroom

16:34.619 --> 16:37.281
as a flame to the wick of a lamp.

16:38.581 --> 16:40.788
Is that the Bible?

16:41.584 --> 16:44.166
Flagg: Danielle steel, I think.

16:44.587 --> 16:46.293
I ook here.

16:48.674 --> 16:50.881
Nadine.

16:51.719 --> 16:53.584
Nadine.

16:54.680 --> 16:56.796
My love.

17:00.353 --> 17:02.139
You okay, ma'am?

17:02.897 --> 17:06.515
Um, of course I am. Why?

17:06.692 --> 17:08.557
Well, you were having a bad dream.

17:08.694 --> 17:11.151
Must have been a real wowzer
by the sound.

17:11.364 --> 17:13.571
Was it about him?

17:14.200 --> 17:15.485
The walkin dude.

17:16.869 --> 17:18.200
Uh

17:18.871 --> 17:21.032
I don't remember.

17:21.207 --> 17:22.572
Teddy:
We're making real good time.

17:22.708 --> 17:25.916
They must have cleared the road
all the way from julesburg.

17:26.087 --> 17:28.203
How long till we get there?

17:28.339 --> 17:31.297
Two hours. Three at the most.

17:31.467 --> 17:33.128
Look, you can see the mountains.

18:15.469 --> 18:18.336
Stu: Summer's almost gone.
Can't believe it.

18:20.099 --> 18:23.842
Glen: How the time flies when you're
having fun, right, east Texas?

18:25.438 --> 18:26.848
How so?

18:29.275 --> 18:32.142
Oh, the power station. Oh, yeah.

18:32.320 --> 18:33.685
I can't believe you forgot that.

18:33.863 --> 18:36.570
I didn't forget it. I blocked it out.

18:36.741 --> 18:39.824
The plague took the people, but it
couldn't take the gadgets, could it?

18:39.994 --> 18:41.905
No, they're all still out there.

18:42.079 --> 18:45.446
Everything from electric can openers
to cobalt bombs,

18:45.625 --> 18:48.458
just waiting for someone
to come along and pick them up.

18:48.628 --> 18:51.085
And the scavenger hunt starts today.

18:51.255 --> 18:52.791
Now, hell, professor.

18:52.965 --> 18:55.798
What's so bad about putting
the rocks back in people's scotch?

18:56.010 --> 18:59.969
Glen: It's the old way.
And the old way was a death trip.

19:00.097 --> 19:01.657
That's a little heavy, don't you think?

19:01.849 --> 19:03.339
Do you?

19:03.768 --> 19:07.056
There's an old woman down there who
might tell you different, east Texas.

19:07.271 --> 19:10.354
If she'd talk about this end of it at all,
that is.

19:10.566 --> 19:11.931
What's the problem?

19:12.109 --> 19:13.474
Glen:
I don't know if there is one.

19:14.153 --> 19:17.361
But I know I'm very concerned
about the way things are going.

19:17.531 --> 19:19.647
She wants a mass meeting.

19:20.368 --> 19:24.202
Except she says it's really god
who wants the meeting.

19:24.372 --> 19:27.660
We say, "fine. You're fine, mother.
God's fine too."

19:27.833 --> 19:30.370
And then we go right back
to tinkering with the power station,

19:30.503 --> 19:31.788
trying to re-create the world

19:31.962 --> 19:34.419
that damn near choked
the human race to death.

19:34.632 --> 19:37.123
What's wrong with this picture?

19:58.197 --> 20:01.030
Well, take a look at that.

20:06.205 --> 20:07.205
Wait

20:50.458 --> 20:53.916
You're all welcome here.

20:54.086 --> 20:58.420
Come on, now.
Come on up and say howdy.

21:09.894 --> 21:12.101
Flagg: Go to her

21:17.902 --> 21:20.769
You're real. You're really real.

21:20.905 --> 21:22.736
No, get up. I ain't no god.

21:22.823 --> 21:25.610
And I ain't gonna be
no golden calf either.

21:25.743 --> 21:28.155
Zellman: Dave zellman.
Rouse's point, New York.

21:28.329 --> 21:29.819
I dreamed of you, mother abagalil.

21:29.997 --> 21:32.534
Abagail:
Oh, I'm so glad to have you come.

21:32.708 --> 21:35.916
I'm Marcy halloran, mother abagall,
from Cleveland.

21:36.086 --> 21:37.747
I dreamed of you too.

21:41.050 --> 21:42.335
Man: Mother abagail, I'm...

21:42.510 --> 21:43.545
Larry.

21:43.719 --> 21:45.425
Larry: She's so gray, St...

21:45.596 --> 21:46.711
Stu: Who?

21:46.889 --> 21:48.049
Larry: I know her.

21:48.724 --> 21:50.009
Hey, hold it.

21:53.979 --> 21:55.264
Abagail: All right, dear.

21:55.439 --> 21:59.648
Come on. Oh, yes, yes. Yes.

22:00.152 --> 22:02.063
Who's this woman who comes?

22:04.865 --> 22:06.696
Flagg: Go to her

22:10.621 --> 22:12.828
my name is Nadine cross.

22:12.998 --> 22:15.284
Mayhap it is and mayhap it ain't.

22:16.335 --> 22:17.871
I'm from New York.

22:18.045 --> 22:19.410
Abagail: Mayhap you are.

22:19.547 --> 22:21.663
And mayhap I ain't.

22:22.550 --> 22:24.711
I won't keep you long.

22:26.512 --> 22:28.628
You look so tired.

22:28.806 --> 22:33.391
Of course, anyone your age
is bound to tire easily, isn't that so?

22:33.978 --> 22:35.639
Joe: Mother abagail.

22:36.438 --> 22:39.271
Hello, Joe. What do you know?
Ha-ha-ha.

22:41.110 --> 22:44.068
- What the hell?
Nadine: Leave me alone, please.

22:49.201 --> 22:51.283
Hello, Nadine.

22:55.541 --> 22:58.157
You gonna leave again
without saying goodbye?

22:58.586 --> 22:59.586
I said I had my reasons.

22:59.753 --> 23:01.633
I didn't wanna answer
questions and still don't,

23:01.797 --> 23:02.832
so just leave me alone.

23:25.529 --> 23:28.396
I'm ready, Brad.
All battery power is up and running.

23:33.704 --> 23:36.787
Listen up, folks.
We're about ready to go for it here.

23:37.666 --> 23:41.500
It might not be such a bad idea
to keep the nearest exit in mind.

23:46.008 --> 23:49.000
Okay, sweetheart. Let's light them up.

24:00.064 --> 24:02.055
I'm scared.

24:03.275 --> 24:05.687
I'm a little scared myself.

24:06.987 --> 24:11.071
- Green board. I've got green across.
Brad: All right.

24:32.304 --> 24:35.137
Ladies and gentlemen, we are back!

24:35.265 --> 24:37.176
Yeah

24:52.282 --> 24:55.945
Abagail: There was something
in that woman this morning.

24:56.370 --> 24:57.576
Was it him?

24:58.372 --> 25:01.785
I don't know, lord,
she passed on by so quick.

25:02.918 --> 25:05.955
No that ain't it.

25:06.130 --> 25:09.748
And I'm too old to be making excuses

25:09.925 --> 25:13.463
to the god of my understanding.

25:17.141 --> 25:20.349
I have sinned in complacency

25:20.519 --> 25:23.431
and sinned in pride.

25:23.605 --> 25:26.597
Sitting back in my rocker like a queen,

25:26.775 --> 25:28.811
and letting them come to me.

25:28.986 --> 25:32.774
Letting them do everything
but bow down before me.

25:32.906 --> 25:34.487
Oh, my lord.

25:34.658 --> 25:37.024
Oh, what am I to do?

25:37.536 --> 25:40.118
Show me how to go, lord.

25:40.956 --> 25:42.947
I'm listening.

27:30.149 --> 27:32.231
Stu: This ain't on the...

27:36.905 --> 27:39.521
Guess we're all gonna
have to get used to this again, huh?

27:50.919 --> 27:53.706
Uh, what I started to say was,

27:53.881 --> 27:57.590
I wonder if maybe we couldn't start
by singing the national anthem.

28:03.432 --> 28:07.892
O say can you see

28:08.061 --> 28:13.101
by the dawn's early light

28:13.233 --> 28:18.899
what so proudly we hailed

28:19.031 --> 28:24.321
at the twilight's last gleaming

28:24.494 --> 28:29.955
whose broad stripes
and bright stars

28:30.125 --> 28:35.210
through the perilous fight

28:35.380 --> 28:40.750
o'er the ramparts we watched

28:40.928 --> 28:46.514
were so gallantly streaming?

28:46.683 --> 28:52.019
And the rockets' red glare

28:52.189 --> 28:57.149
the bombs bursting in air

28:57.903 --> 29:03.443
gave proof through the night

29:03.617 --> 29:08.987
that our flag was still there

29:09.665 --> 29:17.665
o say does that
star-spangled banner yet wave

29:23.387 --> 29:30.350
O'er the land of the free

29:30.519 --> 29:38.519
and the home of the brave?

29:59.840 --> 30:02.832
Abagail: Thy will be done, lord.

30:08.473 --> 30:11.556
Well, I'm pretty nervous up here,
so I hope you'll all bear with me.

30:11.727 --> 30:12.967
Man: We will, St...

30:15.856 --> 30:17.016
Hey, I'm on this.

30:17.190 --> 30:19.101
I'll make this as painless as possible

30:19.234 --> 30:21.725
so we can all get out of here
and have a beer.

30:31.330 --> 30:32.365
Stu: First off,

30:32.539 --> 30:37.579
I'd like you to meet the man
who got the juice on again.

30:37.753 --> 30:41.211
Brad kitchner, stand up, take a bow.

30:48.889 --> 30:52.507
Okay, next thing's
this so-called free zone committee.

30:52.684 --> 30:55.551
The names
came from mother abagail.

30:56.313 --> 30:57.519
Where 1s mother abagail?

30:57.647 --> 31:00.059
- I haven't seen her all day.
Stu: But this is still America.

31:00.233 --> 31:02.144
I'm sure she's around someplace.

31:02.277 --> 31:06.111
And I guess whatever starts with her
still has to end with us.

31:06.323 --> 31:08.029
That means a vote.

31:08.158 --> 31:11.616
First, though, I'd like you to meet
the folks you'll be voting on.

31:11.787 --> 31:13.448
I'm one of them.

31:13.872 --> 31:16.363
Stu redman from arnette, Texas.

31:23.048 --> 31:28.008
Next is Nick andros,
originally from Ridley, Pennsylvania.

31:28.178 --> 31:31.341
And Ralph brentner from okie city.

31:37.229 --> 31:40.892
Miss Frances goldsmith
from ogunquit, Maine.

31:41.066 --> 31:43.808
Stand up, frannie. Let them see
how pretty you look with a dress on.

31:49.991 --> 31:52.357
Brad kitchner's good friend,
Susan stern

31:52.536 --> 31:54.948
from Tacoma, Washington.

31:59.418 --> 32:02.785
Mr. Glen Bateman
from woodsville, New Hampshire.

32:02.963 --> 32:06.672
And Larry Underwood
from New York City.

32:15.225 --> 32:17.328
- You see where Lucy and Joe went?
Stu: Those are the names

32:17.352 --> 32:19.183
mother abagall told us
to put on the list.

32:19.271 --> 32:21.011
Maybe she took him to the bathroom.

32:21.273 --> 32:24.686
If any of you other folks
have any other ideas...

32:24.860 --> 32:28.523
Harold:
Mr. chairman. Mr. chairman?

32:34.411 --> 32:37.198
Chair recognizes Harold lauder.

32:39.875 --> 32:44.539
I move that we accept
mother abagail's free zone committee

32:45.213 --> 32:47.078
in Toto.

32:47.257 --> 32:49.464
If they'll all serve, that is.

32:51.011 --> 32:54.094
Brilliant, utterly brilliant.

32:57.893 --> 33:00.134
Judge, can we do that?

33:01.438 --> 33:02.803
You're damn right, you can.

33:02.981 --> 33:05.848
And I, for one,
think it's a damn good idea.

33:07.110 --> 33:11.695
Folks, it's been moved
and seconded that we accept

33:11.865 --> 33:15.073
the entire committee
as listed on the agenda.

33:15.619 --> 33:17.860
I guess I ought to ask

33:17.996 --> 33:20.533
if there's anybody on the list
who wants to step down.

33:24.794 --> 33:27.752
A voice vote will do just fine.

33:30.634 --> 33:34.547
Well, those in favor of accepting
the committee as it stands?

33:34.679 --> 33:36.795
Sea eas a eat

33:36.973 --> 33:38.679
opposed?

