You? Me.

56:54.036 --> 56:55.992
And I'm gonna stay that way

56:56.163 --> 56:59.701
because it's for someone else
to change it.

57:00.918 --> 57:02.408
Who?

57:03.086 --> 57:05.202
Don't be dense, Harold.

57:05.380 --> 57:07.871
But we can still do things.

57:08.425 --> 57:11.167
Things you wouldn't believe.

57:11.345 --> 57:14.883
Everything but that one thing,
and it's such a little thing really.

57:16.350 --> 57:17.965
How would you know?

57:28.779 --> 57:33.273
Pull tab a, Harold. And shut up.

57:40.791 --> 57:42.452
To new acquaintances.

57:47.547 --> 57:49.503
And absent friends.

58:31.967 --> 58:34.083
Farris:
The disappearance of the old woman

58:34.261 --> 58:37.048
might just be for the best.

58:37.764 --> 58:40.756
People should be free
to judge for themselves

58:40.934 --> 58:43.550
what the lights in the sky are.

58:43.729 --> 58:48.098
Or if god sometimes
does speak in the thunder.

58:48.233 --> 58:50.975
You think she's dead. No.

58:51.111 --> 58:52.726
She should be.

58:52.904 --> 58:58.399
But I don't think she's done yet,
or done with us.

59:00.954 --> 59:03.616
Look, uh, judge,

59:04.332 --> 59:06.038
I wanted to talk to you.

59:06.209 --> 59:09.827
There's no need
to twist yourself into knots, Larry.

59:12.299 --> 59:14.836
I know why I'm here.

59:15.427 --> 59:16.712
And I accept.

59:17.345 --> 59:19.085
